messages.content: ComfyUI-StyleGan is a basic support for StyleGAN2 and StyleGAN3 models in ComfyUI.
Where can I find the original StyleGAN2 and StyleGAN3 models?
The original StyleGAN2 and StyleGAN3 models can be found at https://github.com/NVlabs/stylegan3.
Where should I place the models to use with ComfyUI-StyleGan?
To use models with ComfyUI-StyleGan, place them in the 'ComfyUI/models/stylegan/*.pkl' directory, creating the folder if it doesn't exist.
What are the installation requirements for ComfyUI-StyleGan?
ComfyUI-StyleGan requires CUDA Toolkit, ninja, and either GCC (Linux) or Visual Studio (Windows) for installation.
What is the expected performance of ComfyUI-StyleGan after installation?
Once installed, ComfyUI-StyleGan can generate images at a rate of 64 images/sec on a 3090 with a large batch, though ComfyUI's tensor to PIL for previews may limit it to around 8 fps.
What message will I see when running a StyleGAN workflow for the first time?
When running a StyleGAN workflow for the first time, you will see a message indicating that PyTorch plugins are being built, which should take 30-60s.
Which PyTorch plugins are set up for StyleGAN2 and StyleGAN3?
For StyleGAN2, the 'bias_act_plugin' and 'upfirdn2d_plugin' PyTorch plugins are set up. For StyleGAN3, the 'bias_act_plugin' and 'filtered_lrelu_plugin' are set up.
